by Citigroup in February 2011. Citigroup's ownership was temporary, as EMI announced in November 2011 that it would sell its music arm to Vivendi's Universal Music Group for $1.9 billion and its publishing business to a Sony/ATV consortium for around $2.2 billion. Other members of the Sony consortium include the estate of Michael Jackson, the Blackstone Group, and the Abu Dhabi–owned Mubadala Development Company. EMI's locations in the United Kingdom, the United States, and Canada were all disassembled to repay debt, but the primary head office located outside those countries is still functional.EMI Music Publishing is now owned by Sony/ATV Music Publishing, the music publishing division of Sony Music which bought another 70% stake in EMI Music Publishing.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-09-05T19:31:45.109349+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 5798, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EMI"}], "uuid": "4095b033-8cd5-4a9b-a457-151a492444b6", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "111092", "external_references": [{"id": 32634, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q183412"}, {"id": 54381, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "153494571"}, {"id": 54382, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "no97009953"}, {"id": 54383, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "viaf-153494571"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-17T10:46:22.451444+11:00"}, {"id": 14658, "name": "Victor Lindgren", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 856330, "title": "One of many", "work_id": 71141, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2712842, "title": "Elp: what's to be done", "work_id": 67119, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 856260, "title": "Ombudsman", "work_id": 71084, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 856149, "title": "Not wanted: pollution"